{{Shrine |Image=[[File:Tousho Shrine.jpg|250px]] {{maplink2|frame=yes|plain=yes|type=point|zoom=14|frame-align=center|frame-width=250|coord={{coord|35|17|06.3|N|138|35|43.05|E}}}} |Name=Tousho Shrine |Location=Kitayama 2018, {{ill|Fujinomiya|ja|富士宮市}}, {{ill|Shizuoka Prefecture|ja|静岡県}}, Japan |Latitude degrees=35 |Latitude minutes=17 |Latitude seconds=06.3 |North/South=N |Longitude degrees=138 |Longitude minutes=35 |Longitude seconds=43.05 |East/West=E |Map Country Code=JP |Deity=[[Susanoo-no-Mikoto]]{{Sfn|History of Sengen Shrine|1929|p=510}} }}
'''Tousho Shrine''' (當所神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社}} located in Kitayama, {{ill|Fujinomiya|ja|富士宮市}}, {{ill|Shizuoka Prefecture|ja|静岡県}}, Japan.
== Overview == The shrine was formerly a subordinate shrine (摂社) of the {{ill|Fujisan Hongū Sengen Taisha|ja|富士山本宮浅間大社}} and maintains a strong historical connection with it. For example, the {{ill|Tenbun|ja|天正}} 5 (1577) "Fujisan Hongū Sengen Shrine Ritual Records" (『富士大宮神事帳』) lists the "Kitayama Tousho Shrine Ritual" as one of the annual New Year ceremonies.<ref>{{Sfn|Collected Sengen Documents|1973|p=6}}{{Sfn|Goda|2004|p=41}}</ref>
Additionally, the "List of Annual Ceremonies for Fujisan Hongū" (『富士本宮年中祭礼之次第』), which has a colophon dated {{ill|Keian|ja|慶安}} 3 (1650), also references the "Kitayama Tousho Shrine Ritual" under New Year activities.<ref>{{Sfn|Collected Sengen Documents|1973|p=18}}</ref>
== References == === Sources === {{脚注ヘルプ}} {{Reflist}}
== Bibliography == * {{Cite book|和書 |author = Sengen Shrine Office |year = 1929 |title = History of Sengen Shrine |series = Studies on Mount Fuji |publisher = Kokon Shoin |isbn = |ref = {{SfnRef|History of Sengen Shrine|1929}} }} * {{Cite book|和書 |author = Sengen Shrine Office |year = 1973 |title = Collected Sengen Documents |series = |publisher = Meicho Kankokai |isbn = |ref = {{SfnRef|Collected Sengen Documents|1973}} }} *{{Cite journal|和書 |author = Takaki Goda |date = 2004 |title = Regional Networks of Fujisan Hongū Sengen Taisha during the Sengoku Period: An Analysis of the "Fujisan Hongū Ritual Records" |journal = Takeda Clan Studies |issue = 30 |isbn = |pages = 30-51 |ref = {{SfnRef|Goda|2004}} }}
