'''Tousho Shrine''' (當所神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located in Kitayama, {{ill|Fujinomiya|ja|富士宮市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Shizuoka Prefecture|ja|静岡県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Japan.

== Overview ==
The shrine was formerly a subordinate shrine (摂社) of the {{ill|Fujisan Hongū Sengen Taisha|ja|富士山本宮浅間大社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and maintains a strong historical connection with it. For example, the {{ill|Tenbun|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 5 (1577) "Fujisan Hongū Sengen Shrine Ritual Records" (『富士大宮神事帳』) lists the "Kitayama Tousho Shrine Ritual" as one of the annual New Year ceremonies.<ref>{{Sfn|Collected Sengen Documents|1973|p=6}}{{Sfn|Goda|2004|p=41}}</ref>

Additionally, the "List of Annual Ceremonies for Fujisan Hongū" (『富士本宮年中祭礼之次第』), which has a colophon dated {{ill|Keian|ja|慶安|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 3 (1650), also references the "Kitayama Tousho Shrine Ritual" under New Year activities.<ref>{{Sfn|Collected Sengen Documents|1973|p=18}}</ref>

